adh_short Belongs to the short-chain dehydrogenases reductases (SDR) family

IMS,IMS_C,IMS_HHH Poorly processive, error-prone DNA polymerase involved in untargeted mutagenesis. Copies undamaged DNA at stalled replication forks, which arise in vivo from mismatched or misaligned primer ends. These misaligned primers can be extended by PolIV. Exhibits no 3'-5' exonuclease (proofreading) activity. May be involved in translesional synthesis, in conjunction with the beta clamp from PolIII
Abhydrolase_1,Abhydrolase_4 hydrolases or acyltransferases (alpha beta hydrolase superfamily)

ArsC Interferes with activator-stimulated transcription by interaction with the RNA polymerase alpha-CTD. May function to globally reduce transcription of genes involved in growth- and development-promoting processes and to increase transcription of genes involved in thiol homeostasis, during periods of extreme stress
